  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "atMuUNUm6/hPBLS8PAozMhD+Xu4=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:43.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "Generate with `ph generate --processor <name> --processor-type relationalDb --document-types <type>`. Creates: processor class (extends `RelationalDbProcessor<DB>`), migrations.ts (up/down functions with Kysely-style schema builder), factory.ts (creates namespaced DB per drive), schema.ts (generated TypeScript types from migration via `ph generate --migration-file`). The processor lifecycle: `initAndUpgrade()` runs migrations on startup, `onOperations()` handles each batch, `onDisconnect()` cleans up. Namespaces (`getNamespace(driveId)`) prevent data collisions between drives. Data is exposed through subgraphs via `TodoIndexerProcessor.query(driveId, relationalDb)` for type-safe SQL queries.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:43.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:43.000Z"
    }
  },
